Reasoning: 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is the most likely category as the paper presents a numerical algorithm for finding clusters of complex zeros of a system of polynomials. 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is also likely as the paper deals with polynomial systems and their roots. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is relevant as the algorithm involves subdivision of a polybox in $\mathbb{C}^n$. 
- cs.DS (Dynamical Systems) is relevant as the paper deals with the behavior of complex zeros of polynomial systems. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with the clustering of complex zeros of a system of polynomials, which is a problem in control theory.
